cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it deals with obstacle detection for autonomous navigation in unmanned surface vehicles. The use of a deep encoder-decoder architecture and a novel loss function also suggests that it may fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category as it addresses the issue of false positives in obstacle detection.
